               <p>CHARLES HOULDEN. I live in <placeName id="t18310217-232-crimeloc1360">Rawstorne-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310217-232-crimeloc1360" type="placeName" value="Rawstorne-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310217-232-crimeloc1360" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310217-232-off1358 t18310217-232-crimeloc1360"></join>, and am an <rs id="t18310217-232-viclabel1361" type="occupation">ivory-turner</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310217-232-victim2171 t18310217-232-viclabel1361"></join> - the prisoner was my foreman for about twelve months. On the 14th of February I missed a coat, waistcoat, trousers, and two shirts - I got the officer, who took the prisoner; he denied it, but I told him I had seen the articles - I then went to his lodging, at No. 28, Rawstorne-street; he then delivered up to the officer two shirts, a pair of trousers, and a waistcoat - he then went to another room, unlocked a trunk, and gave out a coat - I know the coat, waistcoat, and trousers are mine, and I believe the shirts are; the officer took some pieces of ivory from a trunk, and some from a drawer in the room.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. BARRY. Q. Had he not been employed by you before this last time? A. Yes - I know part of his family; I believe they are respectable.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310217-232-person2172">
                  JOHN 
                  MURPHY
               <interp inst="t18310217-232-person2172" type="surname" value="MURPHY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-232-person2172" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310217-232-person2172" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Police-officer. I took the prisoner on the 15th of January - I went to his lodgings with him, and the prosecutor followed us there - the prisoner took some things from a drawer; I found these ivory articles in the bottom of the chest of drawers - he then produced this coat from a trunk, and I found some more ivory there.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 23.</p>
